ch.powerunit.collector

Class CollectorTester<T,A,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.powerunit.collector.CollectorTester<T,A,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the input type of the Collector .
    A - the accumulator type of the Collector.
    R - the return type of the Collector.

    @TestInterface(value=ch.powerunit.collector.impl.CollectorTesterImpl.class)
public final class CollectorTester<T,A,R>
extends Object
    This is a tester for Collector.

    The goal of this tester is to validate a Collector. The following tests are done :

    1. accumulator() must return a not null result.
    2. combiner() must return a not null result.
    3. finisher() must return a not null result.
    4. supplier() must return a not null result.
    5. characteristics() must return a not null result and be the same list that is specified in this tester.
    6. For each received sample either use it - withInput - or create a stream - withStreamFromList or withParallelStreamFromList - and then execute the method collect with the Collector under test and validate the returned result.
    Since:
    0.4.0
    Author:
    borettim
